<span id="iv.7.viii-p9"></span>*Rejoice not, my enemy, on my account;  
Though I have fallen, I have risen;  
Though I shall sit in darkness,  
Jehovah* will be *a light to me.*

<span id="iv.7.viii-p10"></span>There are no copies which give a
different reading as to the verb “I have risen.” *Newcome* follows the
Septuagint, and thinks that a conversive <span
id="iv.7.viii-p10.1"></span>ו is left out. It ought rather perhaps to be
considered as the language of faith, realizing the event before it
arrived. The fall and “the darkness” refer no doubt to the outward
calamities of the Church, its troubles and afflictions. — *Ed.*

